The Core Idea: System 1 vs. System 2 ThinkingTo understand CoT, it helps to think about human psychology. Humans have two modes of thinking:System 1 (Fast/Intuitive): If someone asks you, "What is 2 + 2?", your brain instantly blabs out "4" without thinking.System 2 (Slow/Deliberate): If someone asks you, "What is $34 \times 87$?", you cannot answer instantly. You have to grab a piece of paper, multiply the digits step-by-step, carry the numbers, and arrive at the answer.

