REACT: SYNERGIZING REASONING AND ACTING IN LANGUAGE MODELS
If Chain-of-Thought gives an LLM a "scratchpad" to calculate answers, ReAct gives the LLM hands to interact with the world.
The ReAct (Reasoning and Acting) framework is a paradigm that combines Chain-of-Thought (CoT) reasoning with action execution (tool use) in Large Language Models.
Thought->Action->Observation->Thought->Action->Observation
